@aaronw Unfortunately, after reviewing the statute and case law, I don't believe we have any action against Derby City Gaming for overserving her, even if it did contribute to the collision. The KRS makes the individual "primarily liable" and the proximate cause of any injuries. Legislative history makes pretty clear the intention of the dram shop act was to protect injured third-parties, not the individual being served. See KRS 413.241.

